</div><section id="my-judgment" class="level3">
<h3 class="anchored" data-anchor-id="my-judgment">My judgment</h3>
<p>I find julia’s feature a little annoying especially for data science projects.</p>
</section>
</div>
</section>
<section id="string-interpolation" class="level2">
<h2 class="anchored" data-anchor-id="string-interpolation">String interpolation</h2>
<p>In julia, you can insert/interpolate variables into a string using the <code>$</code> sign. You can do the same in R either using inbuilt functions like <code>paste()</code>, <code>paste0()</code>, <code>sprintf()</code>, or with external packages such as the <code>{glue}</code> R package.</p>
